<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB03502</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT AMENDING REPUBLIC ACT NO. 8762, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE RETAIL TRADE LIBERALIZATION ACT, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Intends to minimize barriers to foreign investment as regards to equity and capitalization requirements stated in the Trade Liberalization Law to create a better and a business and consumer friendly environment in the Philippines.
Proposes amendments to Sec.5 of R.A.No.8762 to read as follows:
"Sec.5. Foreign Equity Participation. - Foreign-owned partnerships, associations and corporations . . . may, upon registration with the SEC and the DTI, or in case of foreign owned single proprietorships, with the DTI, engage or invest in the retail trade business WITH A MINIMUM PAID-UP CAPITAL OF THE EQUIVALENT IN PHILIPPINE PESO OF TWO HUNDRED THOUSAND US DOLLARS (US$200,000.00).
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SILVERIO, LORNA C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-08-06</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB00059</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CONSOLIDATED WITH:&nbspHB00192, HB00344, HB00402, HB01222, HB04484, HB04554</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON TRADE AND INDUSTRY ON 2019-08-13</td></tr></table>